# Environment Variables for Rituine

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your values:

```bash
cp .env.local.example .env.local
```

## Variables

```env
# MongoDB connection string from MongoDB Atlas
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@<cluster>.mongodb.net/rituine?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# Secret PIN — only requests with this PIN can modify data
# Set this to any secret string (e.g., "MySecretPin123")
AUTH_PIN=your-secret-pin-here

# This must match AUTH_PIN exactly — used by the frontend to authenticate API calls
NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_PIN=your-secret-pin-here
```

> ⚠️ Never commit your `.env.local` file to git. It's already in `.gitignore`.
